Namespace is use to isolate the resource from dev with prod and other environment. 


Default namespace says the resources are created by the Kubernetes while the cluster is created during first time.


# kubectl get pods (says the pods are under default namesapce)

If we change the current context to set context, then dev can be triggered instead of dafault.
# kubectl config set-context $(kubcetl config current-context) --namespace=dev
# kubectl get pods (says the pods are under dev namespace)

# kubectl get namespace

# kubectl get pod --namespace=dev
# kubectl get pod -n=dev
